The paper deals with lower bounds in arithmetic complexity, which is a subfield of computational complexity theory. The use of rank methods and their limitations are the main focus of the paper. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algebraic geometry, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AG (Algebraic Geometry) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The study of tensor rank and symmetric tensor rank lower bounds indicates a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mention of Waring rank and depth-3 circuits suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
